<div id="review_31018462" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/31018462" />
    <a title="Tempest" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58672-tempest"><img alt="Tempest" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1202579018p2/58672.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/31018462?book_show_action=true">Aug 23, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tempest" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tempest" href="/user/show/58672-tempest">Tempest</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780380754700" href="/book/show/1092438.Gabriela_Clove_and_Cinnamon">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Tempest by: </span>
      Dawn and Kyle, via exhuberant GoodReads ratings
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer31018462" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10637453925538689606">This novel is about a town organized almost exclusively around sex and violence, but through a growing prosperity is suddenly having to reconsider this fundamental structure and become &apos;civilized&apos;. The plot teeters back and forth between the town&apos;s upcoming election and the romance between a poor woman and a rich man. In both circumstances, there is a direct conflict between what is and what, inevitably, will be.<br/><br/>Phoenix-like, the couple loves, then hates, then loves again. The idea seems to be t</span>
  <span id="freeText10637453925538689606" style="display:none">This novel is about a town organized almost exclusively around sex and violence, but through a growing prosperity is suddenly having to reconsider this fundamental structure and become 'civilized'. The plot teeters back and forth between the town's upcoming election and the romance between a poor woman and a rich man. In both circumstances, there is a direct conflict between what is and what, inevitably, will be.<br /><br />Phoenix-like, the couple loves, then hates, then loves again. The idea seems to be that the core of something, whether it is a person or a town, is unalterable. It can be gussied up, but will eventually re-emerge as raw and dirty as it began, only to be gussied up once more. <br /><br />Stimulating and titillating; rhythmic and poetic. Timeless, etc. A good book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10637453925538689606" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


