    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_277450860" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/277450860" />
    <a title="Candace Bethea" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7382459-candace-bethea"><img alt="Candace Bethea" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/277450860?book_show_action=true">Feb 14, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Candace Bethea" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Candace Bethea" href="/user/show/7382459-candace-bethea">Candace Bethea</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer277450860" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6843038778821493818">Gabriela, Clove and Cinnamon is an inspiring love story in which a man loves a woman and the people of Ilheus love their home. The relationship between the people and Ilheus is the first that is illustrated in the novel. Ilheus is a city that is socially in limbo between its cultural, Brazilian roots and the progress that the cacao industry promises. The politics of Ilheus are also reflected in the bar owned by Mr. Nacib, a central character who eventually falls in love. His bar experiences ups </span>
  <span id="freeText6843038778821493818" style="display:none">Gabriela, Clove and Cinnamon is an inspiring love story in which a man loves a woman and the people of Ilheus love their home. The relationship between the people and Ilheus is the first that is illustrated in the novel. Ilheus is a city that is socially in limbo between its cultural, Brazilian roots and the progress that the cacao industry promises. The politics of Ilheus are also reflected in the bar owned by Mr. Nacib, a central character who eventually falls in love. His bar experiences ups and downs, gains and losses, success and hardship, but ultimately Nacib strives to better his business while still holding on to certain aspects that the bar has already had. <br />The relationship between Gabriela and Nacib is the story of a man who falls in love with a woman for both her kindred spirit and her usefulness to him. Nacib hires Gabriela originally as a cook in his bar, but he becomes honey in her hands and the two find themselves deeply in love.<br />This novel has a plot that is absolutely captivating, but the writing itself is dry and tedious to get through. The language itself I found to be only moderately captivating, which also left me bored with the setting and some of the plot.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6843038778821493818" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

