<div id="review_276094572" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/276094572" />
    <a title="Sofia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3666381-sofia"><img alt="Sofia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1372276700p2/3666381.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/276094572?book_show_action=true">Feb 11, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sofia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sofia" href="/user/show/3666381-sofia">Sofia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer276094572" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6486203953200608989">Gabriela, Clove and Cinnamon written by Jorge Amado is an exquisite novel about a love story. Alongside the love story of Nacib and Gabriela, the author tells the story of Ildéus by describing its progress, its political rivalry, its people and their traditions. Jorge Amado writes an extensive but enticing story that brings along the reader who is led to recognize, without a doubt, the beauty of the narrative. This novel reveals the nature of Ilhéus and how in this place, people resist change an</span>
  <span id="freeText6486203953200608989" style="display:none">Gabriela, Clove and Cinnamon written by Jorge Amado is an exquisite novel about a love story. Alongside the love story of Nacib and Gabriela, the author tells the story of Ildéus by describing its progress, its political rivalry, its people and their traditions. Jorge Amado writes an extensive but enticing story that brings along the reader who is led to recognize, without a doubt, the beauty of the narrative. This novel reveals the nature of Ilhéus and how in this place, people resist change and hold onto their traditional culture; by presenting a persistent man who strives unsuccessfully to “erase her (Gabriela’s) past and hide the stove burns on her arms” (293), Amado depicts the greater picture: a town withstanding progress and modernity. The use of characterization, imagery and dialogue is essential in bringing this novel to life; it drives the reader to keep on turning the page and discovering Ilhéus, little by little. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6486203953200608989" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


